messages.content: ComfyUI_KytraWebhookHTTP is a custom node in ComfyUI that allows users to convert and send images or videos to a webhook endpoint using Moviepy.
What library does ComfyUI_KytraWebhookHTTP use for converting and sending media?
ComfyUI_KytraWebhookHTTP uses the Moviepy library to convert and send images or videos.
Can ComfyUI_KytraWebhookHTTP be used with any valid webhook URL?
Yes, although originally intended for personal use in Discord, ComfyUI_KytraWebhookHTTP can be used with any valid webhook URL.
ComfyUI_KytraWebhookHTTP was developed by Kytra Selca.
How can users provide feedback or report bugs for ComfyUI_KytraWebhookHTTP?
Users can provide feedback or report bugs for ComfyUI_KytraWebhookHTTP on its GitHub page.
Does ComfyUI_KytraWebhookHTTP support sending both images and videos?
Yes, ComfyUI_KytraWebhookHTTP supports converting and sending both images and videos to a webhook endpoint.
Is ComfyUI_KytraWebhookHTTP an official ComfyUI node?
No, ComfyUI_KytraWebhookHTTP is a custom node developed by Kytra Selca and not an official ComfyUI node.
